1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the integration of SWIPT in mmWave massive MIMO-NOMA systems, which involves the transmission and processing of information. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes a cluster-head selection algorithm and user grouping for efficient transmission in mmWave massive MIMO-NOMA systems, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the use of mmWave technology for efficient transmission of multimedia data in massive MIMO-NOMA systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes an iterative optimization algorithm for joint optimization of power allocation and power splitting factors, which involves control and optimization of system parameters. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): The paper does not directly relate to this category, but it may have implications for the societal impact of wireless communication technologies.
